’Щ@17b9e8c20e938362e7bb0d16fa9b78ed7df38833f27cc1c69886a23829fd5bbaЪ€Title: title: Nushell 0.41
Path: Fixes
Content:
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/4156] ``save --append``
 will now create a file if missing
 (BraulioVM)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/4135] Upgraded dependencies
 (ahkrr)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/4152] Corrected spelling in crate docs and code docs
 (EdwardBetts)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/4155] Fixed the markup in some of the crate docs
 (tshepang)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/4157] external arguments are now sanitized more
 (BraulioVM)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/4173] upx/strip has been removed after feedback from users
 (fdncred)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/4174] Clipboard capability via arboard removed
 (sophiajt)
[link: https://github.com/nushell/nushell/pull/4178] Removed some unnecessary allocation
 (ahouts)
’Щ@03ee2ceb5a1b52e46a069bcec168c3dc3eae40276d0553e71b241e7650649c0cЪ§Title: title: Nushell 0.41
Path: Engine-q progress
Content:
As engine-q matures, our energy continues to be directed towards it. Over 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q/pulls?page=1&q=is%3Apr+is%3Aclosed] 80 PRs
 have been merged into engine-q since the last Nushell release. As engine-q nears readiness for early adopters to begin using it, we've begun concentrating on closing the remaining gaps in functionality so that it can be used as a daily shell. Once ready, Nushell will have its core functionality replaced by engine-q and from there on we'll be using the new engine. We're planning to change the version number significantly to reflect the jump in features.
’Щ@fe21527f6e73c2a6fd63faee1fae8ad44a5aa2d2d6143852dca2c5ad3e2c96e3ЪЊTitle: title: Nushell 0.41
Path: Looking forward
Content:
As we enter the holidays, the focus of the Nushell effort continues to be on engine-q. There are still 
[link: https://github.com/nushell/engine-q/issues/242] many commands left to port
 and more places to jump in. If you'd like to help, come join us on the 
[link: https://discord.gg/NtAbbGn] discord
. We'd be happy to show you around.
